                            <comment id="12632505" author="sms" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2008 04:12:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-424&quot; title=&quot;nested foreach with flatten and agg gives an error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-424&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-424&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.patch) addresses the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. The schema computation in LOProject used references from its predecessor instead of making a copy. The manipulation of the field schemas altered the schema of the predecessor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Added copy constructors for FieldSchema and Schema&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All unit test cases pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12633005" author="sms" created="Sat, 20 Sep 2008 20:17:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified the earlier patch to be consistent with the use of the copy constructor and made the patch current with SVN&lt;/p&gt;

